  Week 3 Assignment

Now it's time for your week 3 assignment!

This week was all about Cinematic Shots, so naturally the homework will ask you to create various cinematic camera movements. Here are the details:

Your Assignment: Create a Poetic Cinematic Experience

  • Create a Poem written by ChatGPT. Make sure it is around 30 seconds long when read aloud. The poem can be inspiring, silly, serious, or anything in-between. Try to pick a topic that is meaningful and fun to you.
  • Use Your Voice or an AI Voice to create the Narration
  • Create Cinematic Images for the Poem. Try to select images that will work well with camera movement.
  • Cut together at least 5 shots that incorporate camera movements learned this week.
  • Add some music to give your film more emotion.
  • Bonus points for realism. Try to make the TAs question if your trailer was actual footage.

Remember, while the previous two weeks were about pitching and concepts. This week is more about realism. Try to pick shots and scenes that would look realistic with camera movements. This could be drone shots, close-up details, or anything in-between.
